  "prompt": "I'm a 17 year old girl and I'm about to graduate. I want to go to a grad event (\u2018prom\u2019 w/o dancing) but my mother is worried. What should I do?",
  "response": "To help address your mother's concerns, try these steps:\n\n1. Have an open, calm conversation with her:\n- Ask specifically what worries her\n- Listen to her concerns carefully\n- Show her you understand her perspective\n\n2. Address her specific concerns:\n- Discuss transportation safety\n- Share details about the event\n- Introduce her to other students/chaperones going\n- Offer to check in with her during the event\n\n3. Propose compromise solutions:\n- Agree on a specific pickup/drop-off time\n- Share location services on your phone\n- Promise to call/text at certain intervals\n- Suggest she meets the event organizers\n\n4. Be responsible and mature:\n- Show you're taking her concerns seriously\n- Demonstrate you've thought through potential risks\n- Explain why the event is important to you\n\n5. If needed, have a trusted family member or another adult help mediate the conversation\n\nRemember, the goal is to make her feel comfortable while respecting your desire to attend this milestone event. Approach the conversation calmly and thoughtfully.\n\nWould you like help planning how to discuss this with her?",
